{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.4",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 4",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 4 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:1",
      "text": "Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:2",
      "text": "“If one ventures a word with you, will you be offended? Yet who can keep from speaking?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:3",
      "text": "Behold, you have instructed many, and you have strengthened the weak hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:4",
      "text": "Your words have upheld him who was stumbling, and you have made firm the feeble knees.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:5",
      "text": "But now it has come to you, and you are impatient; it touches you, and you are dismayed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:6",
      "text": "Is not your fear of God your confidence, and the integrity of your ways your hope?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:7",
      "text": "“Think now, who that was innocent ever perished? Or where were the upright cut off?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:8",
      "text": "As I have seen, those who plow iniquity and sow trouble reap the same.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:9",
      "text": "By the breath of God they perish, and by the blast of his anger they are consumed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:10",
      "text": "The roar of the lion, the voice of the fierce lion, the teeth of the young lions, are broken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:11",
      "text": "The strong lion perishes for lack of prey, and the whelps of the lioness are scattered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:12",
      "text": "“Now a word was brought to me stealthily, my ear received the whisper of it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:13",
      "text": "Amid thoughts from visions of the night, when deep sleep falls on men,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:14",
      "text": "dread came upon me, and trembling, which made all my bones shake.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:15",
      "text": "A spirit glided past my face; the hair of my flesh stood up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:16",
      "text": "It stood still, but I could not discern its appearance. A form was before my eyes; there was silence, then I heard a voice:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:17",
      "text": "‘Can mortal man be righteous before God? Can a man be pure before his Maker?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:18",
      "text": "Even in his servants he puts no trust, and his angels he charges with error;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:19",
      "text": "how much more those who dwell in houses of clay, whose foundation is in the dust, who are crushed before the moth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:20",
      "text": "Between morning and evening they are destroyed; they perish for ever without any regarding it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.4.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:21",
      "text": "If their tent-cord is plucked up within them, do they not die, and that without wisdom?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
